<item>
            <title>[LU-6350] LFSCK 4: lock the MDT-object based on prediction for preparing bad linkEA </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6350</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, when the namespace LFSCK verifies the object&apos;s linkEA, it will check the linkEA without ldlm/dt lock firstly, if finds inconsistency, it will acquire the ldlm/dt lock on the object, then re-check the linkEA, if still invalid, it will repair the bad linkEA. For the system containing many inconsistent objects, such double-check mechanism is inefficient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Be as some improvement, the LFSCK can make some prediction, for example: if former object contains bad linkEA, then when verifies current object, the namespace LFSCK can acquire the ldlm/dt lock on the object in advance; if the prediction is wrong, it will NOT take ldlm/dt lock in advance for next object.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
